An apparent homemade pipe bomb was found behind a Catholic church Sunday afternoon in Philadelphia, according to police. The 18-inch PVC pipe bomb was spotted by a passerby at about 1:40 p.m. at the St. Dominic Catholic Church, Fox News reported, citing local authorities. The device had capped ends and an unknown black powder on it, according to the report. Nearby streets were blocked off as the city’s bomb squad rushed to the scene, the outlet reported. The bomb was safely taken from the Holmesburg section of the city to bomb squad headquarters. No injuries were reported, police said. More information was not immediately available.